<subSubSection id="7C04D95E729AD115760CCCACB8127B62" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6903A3067409044975C7F4988689D5C3" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E91402847593F4557397002739B345D8" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7BE1613B0BFBDAF475B10C12EF5EFD8F" captionStart="Figure 94" captionStartId="F94" captionText="Figure 94. Distribution of Conostegia muriculata." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure94" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96452" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">94</figureCitation>
). Endemic to the Caribbean slope of south eastern Costa Rica and northern Panama, 40-1200 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="66CF04C5819762047FB7423417A93C60" ID-Zenodo-Dep="974229" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure94" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96452" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" start="Figure 94" startId="F94">
