Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4A38DD3559B1A585253164C5D50F89B8" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia muriculata" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muriculata">
<emphasis id="D4B5D252B3A82BE039FAF974E5C84437" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia muriculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C82860DB10EECF04BCE5F467129D7FA0" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<taxonomicName id="E2FE1AA1AE6365644056B1E670B8343A" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia muriculata" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muriculata">
<emphasis id="B395C95688A89D9D0D0BEB207B2F385A" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia muriculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive species recognized by being overall glabrous, pendant inflorescence, purple petals and muriculate seeds. Unfortunately the phylogenetic placement of this species remains unknown. Because of its small flower buds and being almost totally glabrous, it likely belongs in the 
<taxonomicName id="934A8DD35CE3F4D8345BC4230C517612" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="91E4426F8737E3DD0215D1760BBC4195" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex in section 
<taxonomicName id="C7310194A92215647BDF6D68D3720ADA" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Conostegia">
<emphasis id="19EB4CF51A57967DC7C811A66E1589F9" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As in all species in section 
<taxonomicName id="8A56CF128AAE02E08E0F18321CF4C63B" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Conostegia">
<emphasis id="2137D19315C269672E8D45786F1CF6F7" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the style is short (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4B1BB306B968F6A8A114140F9710B1C9" captionStart="Figure 93" captionStartId="F93" captionText="Figure 93. Conostegia muriculata. A Inflorescence B Lateral view of flower C Frontal view of flower. Photographs by Laurencio Martinez." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure93" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96451" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">93</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="46C5CBB13180C1CE0D8587124FCDCCFD" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
mentions the fact that several specimen labels point to an understory habitat and suggests it is probably a shade tolerant species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
